Not needed.<p>Just quickly scroll through the diff (better version here: <a href="https://gist.github.com/anonymous/e5791d5703325b9cf6d1" rel="nofollow">https://gist.github.com/anonymous/e5791d5703325b9cf6d1</a>) and you will immediately see that all that was done is disable/remove a majority of the functionality.<p><pre><code>    AbortProcess (&quot;INSECURE_APP&quot;);
    Print (&quot;WARNING: Using TrueCrypt is not secure&quot;);
</code></pre>
They added exceptions/rose errors/printed warnings everywhere where you could possibly encrypt and all of it reflects their intent at the Sourceforge page.
